O ΥΕ whom wrath consumes 1 who, passion stung, Writhe at defeat, and nurse your agonies ! Shut up your senses, stifle up your ears,

We fall by course of nature’s law, not force Of thunder‚ or of Jove. Great Saturn‚ thou Hast sifted well the atom-universe 3

But for this reason that thou art the king And only blind from sheer supremacy,
